{
  "texts": [
    "This was shown to be a serious concern by Zhou et al. (2021), and efforts to mitigate this effect at the data level were discussed in Section 4.",
    "Despite this, in Sections 6.1 and 7.1 we still found models to overfit to specific publishers and publisher classes, and in Section 7.2 we found a negative correlation between publisher diversity and the magnitude of the generalization gap.",
    "As such, here we directly test the identifiability of the publisher from article content by replacing the misinformation labels with a unique identifier for each publisher.",
    "In other words, instead of classifying into the set {reliable +, unreliable -}, the model classifies into the set of all possible publishers.",
    "Using the same learning algorithm, we find this to be a substantially more difficult task."
  ]
}